text: Mooresville is a town of Limestone County in the state of Alabama, in the United States. It is located southeast of the intersection of Interstate 565 and Interstate 65, and north of Wheeler Lake. The town is between Huntsville and Decatur, and is part of the Huntsville-Decatur Combined Statistical Area; its population as of the 2020 census is 47. == References == == Other websites == *Town website *Mooresville: A Town of Charm & History Category:Towns in Alabama
title: Mooresville, Alabama
